\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Seven-stage pipeline: (1) LLM extracts FOL predicates with span annotations from source text; (2) predicates and rules are loaded into Prolog KB; (3) Prolog execution attempts to prove query via backward chaining; (4) typed failure detector inspects exception term and ontology; (5) type-specific repair prompt is dispatched to LLM; (6) generated repair is verified by re-running Prolog; (7) Type~1 bridge axioms are cached for reuse. The dotted feedback loop from stage~6 back to stage~3 represents iteration if re-verification fails.}}{4}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pipeline}{{1}{4}{Seven-stage pipeline: (1) LLM extracts FOL predicates with span annotations from source text; (2) predicates and rules are loaded into Prolog KB; (3) Prolog execution attempts to prove query via backward chaining; (4) typed failure detector inspects exception term and ontology; (5) type-specific repair prompt is dispatched to LLM; (6) generated repair is verified by re-running Prolog; (7) Type~1 bridge axioms are cached for reuse. The dotted feedback loop from stage~6 back to stage~3 represents iteration if re-verification fails}{figure.1}{}}
