\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Accuracy on ProofWriter depth 3--5 when each repair type is disabled. Type~3 (missing facts) has largest impact ($-4.9$ pp.). Type~1 (lexical mismatch) second ($-4.9$ pp.). Type~2, 4, 5 each contribute 1--2 pp. Type~5 (scope conflicts) has smallest impact on benchmarks, likely due to less frequent scope ambiguity in structured rule-based datasets.}}{12}{figure.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ablation}{{5}{12}{Accuracy on ProofWriter depth 3--5 when each repair type is disabled. Type~3 (missing facts) has largest impact ($-4.9$ pp.). Type~1 (lexical mismatch) second ($-4.9$ pp.). Type~2, 4, 5 each contribute 1--2 pp. Type~5 (scope conflicts) has smallest impact on benchmarks, likely due to less frequent scope ambiguity in structured rule-based datasets}{figure.5}{}}
